hopobject.body: I went to rx-checkout.net Global markets have been shaky this week as traders, worried about a pullback in bond purchases, began dumping bonds. That sent prices lower and yields sharply higher. Money has also flowed out of emerging stock markets, sending the currencies of countries such as Malaysia, Indonesia and India sharply lower. However, U.S. bond yields pulled back Tuesday, bringing relief to investors worried about higher interest rates.
